Job Location: Bahria Town Phase 7, Rawalpindi 

Are you a night owl with excellent communication skills? Do you thrive in handling tricky online situations and enjoy interacting with international clients? If yes, we've got the perfect opportunity for you!

 About Us:
Associated Business Solutions is the backbone of Offshore Operations for our USA-based clients, specializing in online electronics sales. We're seeking a dedicated Entry-Level Business Communication Executive to join our dynamic team. Don't worry if you're new to the field - we provide relevant guidance after training!

 Job Responsibilities:
As a Business Communication Executive, you'll be responsible for:

Handling inbound calls, emails, and chats from clients regarding purchase deals and related issues. 
Interacting with major online marketplaces like eBay, Amazon, Walmart, and PayPal to resolve account queries. 
 Job Details:

Permanent Night Shift (Office-Based)
Working Hours: Mon-Fri, 09:00 PM to 06:00 AM
 Required Skills:
To excel in this role, you'll need:

Excellent command of English (both written and verbal). 
The ability to handle pressure in tricky online call situations. 
Adaptability to manage night shift challenges. 
 Benefits:

Competitive Salary Range: 30,000-40,000 PKR
Provident Fund benefits
Monthly Lavish Dinners
Yearly Leisure Tour to the North
Ready to take your career to new heights? Send your CV to [redacted email address] or WhatsApp us directly at (View phone number). 

Join us at Associated Business Solutions, where every night is an opportunity to shine in the heart of Bahria Town Phase 7, Rawalpindi!

Title: CONTENT CREATOR REQUIRED FOR OUR SOCIAL MEDIA NETWORK
Description:
**Job Title: Content Creator (Video) – Trending News & Social Issues**

**Location:** Various Regions Across Pakistan

**Job Type:** Full-time/Part-time/Freelance

**About Us:**
We are a dynamic media platform committed to delivering insightful and engaging content on trending news and social issues. Our goal is to inform, inspire, and provoke thought among our diverse audience. We are looking for talented content creators from different regions of Pakistan to bring unique perspectives and stories to our platform. 

**Job Description:**
We are seeking passionate and creative individuals to join our team as Content Creators. The ideal candidates will be responsible for producing high-quality video content on trending news and social issues relevant to their region. This role requires staying updated with current events, social trends, and local issues, and being able to present them in a compelling and engaging manner. 

**Responsibilities:**
- Research and stay updated with trending news, social issues, and regional events. 
- Create engaging video content, including scripting, filming, editing, and publishing. 
- Develop content ideas that resonate with the local audience and align with our platform’s objectives. 
- Collaborate with the editorial team to ensure content accuracy and alignment with our brand voice. 
- Utilize various social media platforms to distribute content and engage with the audience. 
- Monitor and analyze the performance of content and make improvements based on feedback and data. 
- Ensure all content is created in accordance with copyright laws and platform policies. 

**Requirements:**
- Proven experience in video content creation (portfolio or sample work required). 
- Strong understanding of social media platforms and video distribution channels. 
- Excellent storytelling and communication skills. 
- Ability to work independently and meet deadlines. 
- Proficiency in video editing software (e. g. , Adobe Premiere, Final Cut Pro, or similar). 
- Familiarity with current trends in digital media and content consumption. 
- Fluent in Urdu and regional languages (Punjabi, Sindhi, Pashto, Balochi, etc. ), with good command of English. 
- A strong network within the community and a keen understanding of local issues. 

**Preferred Qualifications:**
- Previous experience in journalism, media, or related fields. 
- Knowledge of SEO and social media analytics tools. 
- Creative mindset with the ability to think outside the box. 
- Experience in on-camera presentation or hosting. 

**Locations:**
We are looking for content creators from various parts of Pakistan, including but not limited to:
- Karachi
- Lahore
- Islamabad/Rawalpindi
- Peshawar
- Quetta
- Multan
- Hyderabad
- Faisalabad

**How to Apply:**
Interested candidates are encouraged to submit their resume, a cover letter, and a portfolio of their work to [Your Contact Email]. Please specify your region and any particular topics of interest in your application. 

**Deadline:** Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis until the positions are filled. 

Join us in creating impactful content that resonates with audiences and drives meaningful conversations across Pakistan!

**Job Type:** Full-time/Part-time/Freelance

**About Us:**
We are a dynamic media platform committed to delivering insightful and engaging content on trending news and social issues. Our goal is to inform, inspire, and provoke thought among our diverse audience. We are looking for talented content creators from different regions of Pakistan to bring unique perspectives and stories to our platform. 

**Job Description:**
We are seeking passionate and creative individuals to join our team as Content Creators. The ideal candidates will be responsible for producing high-quality video content on trending news and social issues relevant to their region. This role requires staying updated with current events, social trends, and local issues, and being able to present them in a compelling and engaging manner. 

**Responsibilities:**
- Research and stay updated with trending news, social issues, and regional events. 
- Create engaging video content, including scripting, filming, editing, and publishing. 
- Develop content ideas that resonate with the local audience and align with our platform’s objectives. 
- Collaborate with the editorial team to ensure content accuracy and alignment with our brand voice. 
- Utilize various social media platforms to distribute content and engage with the audience. 
- Monitor and analyze the performance of content and make improvements based on feedback and data. 
- Ensure all content is created in accordance with copyright laws and platform policies. 

**Requirements:**
- Proven experience in video content creation (portfolio or sample work required). 
- Strong understanding of social media platforms and video distribution channels. 
- Excellent storytelling and communication skills. 
- Ability to work independently and meet deadlines. 
- Proficiency in video editing software (e. g. , Adobe Premiere, Final Cut Pro, or similar). 
- Familiarity with current trends in digital media and content consumption. 
- Fluent in Urdu and regional languages (Punjabi, Sindhi, Pashto, Balochi, etc. ), with good command of English. 
- A strong network within the community and a keen understanding of local issues. 

**Preferred Qualifications:**
- Previous experience in journalism, media, or related fields. 
- Knowledge of SEO and social media analytics tools. 
- Creative mindset with the ability to think outside the box. 
- Experience in on-camera presentation or hosting. 

**Locations:**
We are looking for content creators from various parts of Pakistan, including but not limited to:
- Karachi
- Lahore
- Islamabad/Rawalpindi
- Peshawar
- Quetta
- Multan
- Hyderabad
- Faisalabad

**How to Apply:**
Interested candidates are encouraged to submit their resume, a cover letter, and a portfolio of their work to [Your Contact Email]. Please specify your region and any particular topics of interest in your application. 

**Deadline:** Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis until the positions are filled. 

Join us in creating impactful content that resonates with audiences and drives meaningful conversations across Pakistan!

Location: Mian Mehmood Ali Kasoori Road, Lahore
Description:
Key Responsibilities:

- Generate weekly procurement demands to ensure timely and cost-effective supply of ingredients and materials
- Maintain a clean, safe, and welcoming environment for customers and staff
- Ensure excellent hygiene standards are met, including food handling, storage, and disposal
- Foster positive customer relationships and resolve any complaints or issues promptly
- Lead and manage a team of staff, providing guidance, training, and support as needed
- Carry out tasks and duties as needed, including hands-on assistance during peak periods
- Monitor and control labor costs, inventory, and other expenses to meet budget targets
- Implement and enforce company policies, procedures, and standards
- Collaborate with other departments (e. g. , marketing, finance) to drive business growth and success
- Analyze sales data and customer feedback to identify areas for improvement and implement changes
- Ensure compliance with all relevant laws, regulations, and industry standards

- 3+ years of experience in restaurant/cafe management or a related field
- Proven track record of success in managing teams and operations
- Strong communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills
- Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and adapt to changing circumstances
- Knowledge of food safety, hygiene, and quality control procedures
- Familiarity with inventory management and cost control techniques
- Excellent customer service skills and a customer-centric approach
- Ability to work varied shifts, including evenings, weekends, and holidays.

Title: hand written assignment
Description:
Writing handwritten assignments involves several steps to ensure clarity, neatness, and proper organization. Here’s a comprehensive guide:

### 1. Preparation
- **Gather Materials:** Ensure you have high-quality paper, a reliable pen or pencil, an eraser, and a ruler. 
- **Understand the Assignment:** Carefully read the instructions, understand the topic, and note any specific requirements regarding length, format, or content. 

### 2. Planning
- **Outline Your Content:** Create a detailed outline of your assignment, breaking it down into introduction, body paragraphs, and conclusion. 
- **Research:** Gather information and take notes, ensuring you have all the necessary facts, quotes, and references. 

### 3. Writing
#### **Introduction**
- Start with a compelling opening sentence. 
- Introduce the main topic and provide context. 
- State your thesis or main argument clearly. 

#### **Body Paragraphs**
- **Structure:** Each paragraph should focus on a single point or idea. 
- **Topic Sentence:** Start each paragraph with a clear topic sentence. 
- **Evidence:** Support your points with evidence, examples, or quotes. 
- **Transition:** Use transitional phrases to ensure smooth flow between paragraphs. 

#### **Conclusion**
- Summarize the main points. 
- Restate the thesis in the context of the information provided. 
- End with a strong closing sentence or a call to action. 

### 4. Presentation
- **Legibility:** Write clearly and legibly. Use cursive or print based on what is more readable. 
- **Spacing:** Leave adequate space between lines and paragraphs for readability. 
- **Margins:** Maintain consistent margins on all sides of the paper. 
- **Headings and Subheadings:** Use headings and subheadings to organize content if applicable. 
- **Indentation:** Indent the first line of each paragraph. 

### 5. Editing and Proofreading
- **Review Content:** Check for completeness, coherence, and relevance. 
- **Grammar and Spelling:** Correct any grammatical or spelling errors. 
- **Clarity and Conciseness:** Ensure sentences are clear and concise. 
- **Revisions:** Make necessary revisions to improve the overall quality of your writing.

Title: We're hiring for Assistant Manager both for Male & Female
Description:
Position: Assistant Manager
Company: Stepup Visa Consultants
Location: Sargodha

About Stepup Visa Consultants:
Stepup Visa Consultants is a leading immigration consultancy firm dedicated to providing comprehensive visa and immigration services to clients worldwide. With a team of experienced professionals and a commitment to excellence, we assist individuals and families in navigating the complex process of obtaining visas and immigrating to their desired destinations. 

Role Overview:
Stepup Visa Consultants is seeking a dynamic and motivated individual to join our team as an Assistant Manager. The Assistant Manager will play a key role in supporting the operations of the consultancy firm, assisting with client management, team coordination, and administrative tasks. 

Responsibilities:
1. 	Client Management: Serve as a primary point of contact for clients, providing guidance and support throughout the visa application process. 
2. 	Team Coordination: Collaborate with consultants and other team members to ensure efficient workflow and timely completion of tasks. 
3. 	Administrative Support: Assist in administrative tasks such as scheduling appointments, managing documents, and maintaining client records. 
4. 	Sales Support: Support the sales team in generating leads, preparing proposals, and following up with potential clients. 
5. 	Quality Assurance: Ensure compliance with visa regulations and company policies to deliver high-quality services to clients. 
6. 	Reporting: Prepare reports and presentations as needed to track progress and performance metrics. 
7. 	Training and Development: Participate in training programs to enhance knowledge of visa regulations and improve client service skills. 

Qualifications:
- Bachelor’s degree in business administration, Immigration Law, or related field. 
- Proven experience in a similar role, preferably in the immigration or consultancy industry. 
- Strong communication and interpersonal skills. 
- Excellent organizational and time management abilities. 
- Proficiency in MS Office suite and client management software. 
- Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple tasks simultaneously. 
- Knowledge of visa regulations and immigration processes is a plus. 

Benefits:
•	Competitive salary package
•	Health insurance coverage
•	Professional development opportunities
•	Friendly and collaborative work environment

How to Apply:
Interested candidates are encouraged to submit their resume and cover letter to stepupvisaconsultants[at]gmail[dot]com with the subject line "Assistant Manager Application - Stepup Visa Consultants. " Please include a brief summary of your relevant experience and why you are interested in joining our team.

Title: Content Creators required
Description:
Job Description: *In-House Content Creator for KrossFits in Multan* 

Overview:
KrossFits is seeking one male and one female  talented and creative In-House Content Creator to join our dynamic content team. This role involves creating engaging and high-quality content for advertisements on Meta (Facebook and Instagram), Tiktok and other social media platforms, as well as producing organic content such as fashion reels and user-generated content (UGC) videos. The position requires working Monday to Saturday from 10 am to 6 pm we can change the timing on your request but working hours will remain the same. 

Responsibilities:
1. *Content Creation for Ads:*
   - Develop and produce visually appealing and compelling ad content for Meta platforms, Tiktok and other social media, aligned with KrossFits' brand identity. 
   - Utilize Meta's ad tools and analytics to optimize content performance. 

2. *Organic Content Development:*
   - Create engaging fashion reels and UGC videos that showcase KrossFits' products and lifestyle to increase organic reach and engagement. 
   - Stay updated with current trends in fashion and social media to ensure content is relevant and appealing. 
   - Work closely with influencers and customers to generate authentic UGC that aligns with KrossFits' brand values. 

3. *Content Strategy and Planning:*
   - Develop a content calendar in coordination with the marketing team to ensure a steady flow of content that supports KrossFits' marketing objectives. 
   - Brainstorm and pitch new content ideas that align with KrossFits' brand objectives and audience interests. 
   - Monitor and analyze content performance to inform future strategies. 

4. *Production and Editing:*
   - Handle all aspects of content production, including filming, editing, and post-production. 
   - Ensure high production quality and consistency across all content. 
   - Use various editing tools and software to enhance video and photo content along with editor. 

5. *Engagement and Community Building:*
   - Collaborate with the social media manager to foster audience interaction and loyalty. 
   - Participate in live sessions and other interactive formats to increase real-time engagement. 

6. *Reporting and Analysis:*
   - Track content performance using social media analytics tools. 
   - Provide regular reports on content reach, engagement, and ROI. 
   - Adjust content strategies based on performance data to maximize effectiveness. 

 Requirements:
- Proven experience or interest as a Content Creator, preferably in the vlogging, fashion or lifestyle industry. 
- Proficiency in content creation easy tools and software. 
- Strong understanding of Meta platforms, TikTok and their ad functionalities. 
- Excellent visual storytelling skills and a keen eye for design. 
- Ability to manage multiple projects and meet deadlines. 
- Strong communication and collaboration skills. 
- Creativity and a passion for fashion and social media trends. 

Working Hours:
- Monday to Saturday, 10 am to 6 pm. 

Compensation:
- Competitive salary commensurate with experience. 

Join the KrossFits team and contribute to our brand's growth by creating captivating content that resonates with our audience and drives engagement!
